      "best_description": "<p>The Oakland Ice Center/Sharks Ice proudly offers a learn to skate program which has been developed especially for athletes with special physical and developmental challenges. Emphasizing fun and safety, the Special Skater program helps to improve balance and coordination which promotes an \"I can do it!\" attitude that carries over into other aspects of the participant's life. With the assistance of volunteers, skaters develop skills, make new friends and experience a new found freedom and sense of accomplishment.</p>\n<h4><span style=\"color: #190d30; font-family: 'DM Sans', Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; background-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);\">Participants are allowed 1 family member to assist skater on ice. Fee includes skate rentals. There are no refunds, makeups, or credits for missed classes.</span></h4>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>"
